{"parentUuid":"ffb064ab-5e91-4545-add1-8c3ef5b6911f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccvwyvc7jKLav1SckTcNh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FNQc1PsSLqbtNvnJBuxaKd","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/surface-delta.md","content":"# Attack-surface delta — GET /v1/usage/daily\n\nBest-effort hint for the security agent's diff reconciliation. The diff\n(`git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others --exclude-standard`) is\nthe source of truth; this file is advisory.\n\n## New entry points\n\n- **`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=YYYY-MM-DD`** — new HTTP route,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py:31` (`get_usage_daily_endpoint`), mounted via\n  `app.include_router(usage_daily_router)` in `src/main.py:90`. Customer-scoped\n  (any authenticated API key; no admin gate) — reads only the caller's own\n  tenant data, derived solely from the authenticated principal\n  (`principal.api_key_id`). Behind the same middleware edge stack as every\n  other route (Tier-1 IP throttle, body-size guard, security headers, CORS)\n  plus a per-route Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` throttle\n  (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py:24`, `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`).\n\n## New trust boundaries\n\n- None. No outbound third-party calls, no new subprocess/exec invocations, no\n  SSRF-capable fetches. The only boundary this route crosses is the existing\n  API↔PostgreSQL boundary (already governed by `scoped_transaction` + RLS) and\n  the existing API↔Redis boundary (Tier-2 throttle, reused unchanged).\n\n## New data flows / sinks\n\n- **New read query**: `aggregate_daily_event_counts` in\n  `src/repositories/usage_repo.py:214-244` — a `SELECT metric, SUM(event_count)\n  ... GROUP BY metric` over the existing `usage_rollup` table, scoped by\n  `api_key_id = :api_key_id` (bound parameter, never client input) as the\n  first predicate, plus the day-window bound parameters (`:day_start`,\n  `:day_end`) derived from the validated `date`. No new table, no new column,\n  no migration. All values are bound parameters — no string interpolation of\n  caller input into SQL text.\n- **No new stored data.** This is a pure read; nothing is written or\n  persisted by this change. No new field, no new data class, no new at-rest\n  control — `data-protection-conventions` is not triggered (confirmed in\n  `plan.md` → *Data / migrations*).\n- **New logged event**: `usage.daily.read` in\n  `src/services/usage_daily_service.py:44-51` —\n  `{userId: api_key_id, action: \"read\", resource: \"usage_rollup\", date:\n  <echoed date string>, metricCount: <int>}`. No `customer_id` value, no\n  metric *values*, no raw request/response body logged — only the count of\n  metrics returned. Routed through the existing `get_logger()` facade\n  (`src/logging/__init__.py`), which applies the centralized redaction +\n  control-character-stripping processors to every log call regardless of\n  call site.\n\n## New privilege / authz surface\n\n- **No new authenticated route class.** The route depends only on\n  `require_api_key` (existing facade, unchanged) — no new admin/scope gate is\n  introduced, and none is required (deliberately: this is a read of the\n  caller's own data, matching `GET /v1/usage`'s posture, not `PUT /v1/quotas`'s\n  admin-gated posture). An ingest-scoped key and an admin-scoped key are both\n  authorized identically; neither can pivot to another tenant's data because\n  the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/`api_key_id` input — the only tenant\n  selector is the authenticated principal itself.\n- No token issuance, no role/permission model change, no widening of what any\n  existing key can reach beyond its own tenant's daily summary.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":189,"cache_read_input_tokens":141576,"output_tokens":1537,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":189},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1537,"cache_read_input_tokens":141576,"cache_creation_input_tokens":189,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":189,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvwyuTfJRdh8tN9iYzHm","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"0ddd4cfb-816a-41ca-b800-76cf57fe98d0","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:04:48.364Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
