{"parentUuid":"3530c59e-f547-442b-912c-d99e2c24e53d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"31d62281-78eb-4b7d-bb8c-b1ec8a71c6f0","agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KrzoBBNik2Sswe6uEgMK5a","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Attack-surface delta — quota administration (GET/DELETE /v1/quotas)\n2\t\n3\tBest-effort hint for the security stage; reconciled against the actual diff, not authoritative.\n4\t\n5\t## New entry points\n6\t\n7\t- `GET /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:59` (`list_quotas_endpoint`). Admin-scoped read of\n8\t  the caller's own tenant's full quota list. No request body/query/path parameter.\n9\t- `DELETE /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:68` (`delete_quota_endpoint`). Admin-scoped\n10\t  removal of one `(customer_id, metric)` cap, identified by query parameters\n11\t  (`customer_id`, `metric`). 204 on success, 404 if absent.\n12\t\n13\tBoth reuse the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency (`src/api/routes/quotas.py:26`)\n14\tverbatim — no new auth path, scope, or dependency chain.\n15\t\n16\t## New trust boundaries\n17\t\n18\tNone. No outbound third-party call, no new subprocess/exec, no new SSRF-capable fetch. Both new\n19\troutes only read/write the existing `quotas` table over the existing `app <-> RDS` boundary\n20\talready used by `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n21\t\n22\t## New data flows / sinks\n23\t\n24\t- `SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id ORDER BY\n25\t  customer_id, metric` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::list_quotas` (parameterized `text()`,\n26\t  no string interpolation).\n27\t- `DELETE FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric =\n28\t  :metric RETURNING customer_id` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::delete_quota` (parameterized\n29\t  `text()`).\n30\t- No new table, no new stored field. Both queries operate on the pre-existing `quotas` table\n31\t  (migration `0003`), which already carries the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS policy.\n32\t- **Stored-field classification (unchanged, no new field):** `customer_id` / `metric` /\n33\t  `limit_per_window` were already classified **non-sensitive operational config** at rest under\n34\t  RDS SSE (storage-level) in the metric-quotas plan. This feature stores no new field — it only\n35\t  reads (GET) and removes (DELETE) existing rows — so no field-level KDF/KMS applies here; the\n36\t  `data_protection_waiver` in `.pipeline/acceptance.md` frontmatter documents this explicitly for\n37\t  the reconciliation.\n38\t- New log event: `quota.delete` (INFO) — `src/services/quota_service.py::delete_tenant_quota`,\n39\t  emitted via the existing structlog facade (`src/logging`), which auto-redacts `customer_id`.\n40\t\n41\t## New privilege / authz surface\n42\t\n43\t- Both new routes are authenticated + admin-scope-gated (`scope == 'admin'`), identical to the\n44\t  existing `PUT /v1/quotas`. No new scope value, no privilege widening beyond what `PUT` already\n45\t  grants an admin key.\n46\t- DELETE is a net-new **destructive** capability (removing a cap re-enables unlimited usage for\n47\t  that `(customer_id, metric)` until a new `PUT`) — mitigated by the same admin-scope gate + tenant\n48\t  isolation (`api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS) already covering `PUT`/GET. This is the STRIDE\n49\t  Elevation-of-Privilege / IDOR-BOLA row the plan calls out (AC8 proves cross-tenant DELETE is\n50\t  invisible, matching zero rows -> 404).\n51\t\n52\t## Other changes\n53\t\n54\t- `src/api/middleware.py` — added `\"DELETE\"` to `CORSMiddleware.allow_methods`. No live-control\n55\t  effect (empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API); completeness only, matching the plan.\n56\t"}]},"uuid":"43a17f72-8bb7-41ea-aac4-17c72b280cda","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:04:50.891Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/surface-delta.md","content":"# Attack-surface delta — quota administration (GET/DELETE /v1/quotas)\n\nBest-effort hint for the security stage; reconciled against the actual diff, not authoritative.\n\n## New entry points\n\n- `GET /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:59` (`list_quotas_endpoint`). Admin-scoped read of\n  the caller's own tenant's full quota list. No request body/query/path parameter.\n- `DELETE /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:68` (`delete_quota_endpoint`). Admin-scoped\n  removal of one `(customer_id, metric)` cap, identified by query parameters\n  (`customer_id`, `metric`). 204 on success, 404 if absent.\n\nBoth reuse the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency (`src/api/routes/quotas.py:26`)\nverbatim — no new auth path, scope, or dependency chain.\n\n## New trust boundaries\n\nNone. No outbound third-party call, no new subprocess/exec, no new SSRF-capable fetch. Both new\nroutes only read/write the existing `quotas` table over the existing `app <-> RDS` boundary\nalready used by `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n\n## New data flows / sinks\n\n- `SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id ORDER BY\n  customer_id, metric` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::list_quotas` (parameterized `text()`,\n  no string interpolation).\n- `DELETE FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric =\n  :metric RETURNING customer_id` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::delete_quota` (parameterized\n  `text()`).\n- No new table, no new stored field. Both queries operate on the pre-existing `quotas` table\n  (migration `0003`), which already carries the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS policy.\n- **Stored-field classification (unchanged, no new field):** `customer_id` / `metric` /\n  `limit_per_window` were already classified **non-sensitive operational config** at rest under\n  RDS SSE (storage-level) in the metric-quotas plan. This feature stores no new field — it only\n  reads (GET) and removes (DELETE) existing rows — so no field-level KDF/KMS applies here; the\n  `data_protection_waiver` in `.pipeline/acceptance.md` frontmatter documents this explicitly for\n  the reconciliation.\n- New log event: `quota.delete` (INFO) — `src/services/quota_service.py::delete_tenant_quota`,\n  emitted via the existing structlog facade (`src/logging`), which auto-redacts `customer_id`.\n\n## New privilege / authz surface\n\n- Both new routes are authenticated + admin-scope-gated (`scope == 'admin'`), identical to the\n  existing `PUT /v1/quotas`. No new scope value, no privilege widening beyond what `PUT` already\n  grants an admin key.\n- DELETE is a net-new **destructive** capability (removing a cap re-enables unlimited usage for\n  that `(customer_id, metric)` until a new `PUT`) — mitigated by the same admin-scope gate + tenant\n  isolation (`api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS) already covering `PUT`/GET. This is the STRIDE\n  Elevation-of-Privilege / IDOR-BOLA row the plan calls out (AC8 proves cross-tenant DELETE is\n  invisible, matching zero rows -> 404).\n\n## Other changes\n\n- `src/api/middleware.py` — added `\"DELETE\"` to `CORSMiddleware.allow_methods`. No live-control\n  effect (empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API); completeness only, matching the plan.\n","numLines":56,"startLine":1,"totalLines":56}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3530c59e-f547-442b-912c-d99e2c24e53d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"43a17f72-8bb7-41ea-aac4-17c72b280cda","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccvx1PK15HSM8XnutohLd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is stale content from the prior quota-admin feature run. Now write the fresh version for this feature."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1594,"cache_read_input_tokens":143345,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1594,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccvx1JLbypDL4dFsnvfyu","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"b1d47ae0-5e62-458e-8234-faea9b8e5e54","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:04:53.997Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"b1d47ae0-5e62-458e-8234-faea9b8e5e54","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccvx1PK15HSM8XnutohLd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JwC4txrgTthot2DUxUURdV","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/surface-delta.md","content":"# Attack-surface delta — GET /v1/usage/daily (per-metric daily usage summary)\n\nBest-effort hint for the security agent's diff reconciliation. The diff\n(`git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others --exclude-standard`) is\nthe source of truth; this file is advisory.\n\n## New entry points\n\n- **`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=YYYY-MM-DD`** — new HTTP route,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py:31` (`get_usage_daily_endpoint`), mounted via\n  `app.include_router(usage_daily_router)` in `src/main.py:90`. Customer-scoped\n  (any authenticated API key; no admin gate) — reads only the caller's own\n  tenant data, derived solely from the authenticated principal\n  (`principal.api_key_id`); the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/`api_key_id`\n  input. Behind the same middleware edge stack as every other route (Tier-1 IP\n  throttle, body-size guard, security headers, CORS) plus a per-route Tier-2\n  per-`api_key_id` throttle (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py:24`,\n  `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`).\n\n## New trust boundaries\n\n- None. No outbound third-party calls, no new subprocess/exec invocations, no\n  SSRF-capable fetches. The only boundaries this route crosses are the\n  existing API↔PostgreSQL boundary (governed by `scoped_transaction` + the\n  existing `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS policy) and the existing\n  API↔Redis boundary (Tier-2 throttle, reused unchanged).\n\n## New data flows / sinks\n\n- **New read query**: `aggregate_daily_event_counts`,\n  `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` (new function, appended after\n  `stream_usage_rollups`) — a `SELECT metric, SUM(event_count) ... GROUP BY\n  metric` over the existing `usage_rollup` table, scoped by `api_key_id =\n  :api_key_id` (bound parameter, from `principal.api_key_id`, never client\n  input) as the first predicate, plus the day-window bound parameters\n  (`:day_start`, `:day_end`) derived from the validated `date`. No new table,\n  no new column, no migration. All values are bound parameters — no string\n  interpolation of caller input into SQL text.\n- **No new stored data.** This is a pure read; nothing is written or\n  persisted by this change. No new field, no new data class, no new at-rest\n  control — `data-protection-conventions` is not triggered (the `usage_rollup`\n  rows it reads were already classified non-sensitive operational metering\n  data by the prior feature's interview; this change adds no new field).\n- **New logged event**: `usage.daily.read`,\n  `src/services/usage_daily_service.py` — `{userId: api_key_id, action:\n  \"read\", resource: \"usage_rollup\", date: <echoed date string>, metricCount:\n  <int>}`. No `customer_id` value, no metric *values*, no raw request/response\n  body logged — only the count of metrics returned. Routed through the\n  existing `get_logger()` facade (`src/logging/__init__.py`), which applies\n  the centralized redaction + control-character-stripping processors to every\n  log call regardless of call site.\n\n## New privilege / authz surface\n\n- **No new authenticated route class.** The route depends only on\n  `require_api_key` (existing facade, unchanged) — no new admin/scope gate is\n  introduced, and none is required (deliberately: this is a read of the\n  caller's own data, matching `GET /v1/usage`'s posture, not `PUT /v1/quotas`'s\n  admin-gated posture). An ingest-scoped key and an admin-scoped key are both\n  authorized identically; neither can pivot to another tenant's data because\n  the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/`api_key_id` input — the only tenant\n  selector is the authenticated principal itself.\n- No token issuance, no role/permission model change, no widening of what any\n  existing key can reach beyond its own tenant's daily summary.\n\n## Other changes\n\n- `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` — additive only: one new frozen dataclass\n  (`DailyMetricCount`) and one new function (`aggregate_daily_event_counts`)\n  appended at the end of the file; every existing function\n  (`find_usage_rollup`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`) is\n  byte-for-byte unchanged.\n- `src/main.py` — one new import + one new `app.include_router(...)` line;\n  every existing router registration and the middleware stack order are\n  unchanged.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1594,"cache_read_input_tokens":143345,"output_tokens":1741,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1594},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1741,"cache_read_input_tokens":143345,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1594,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1594,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccvx1JLbypDL4dFsnvfyu","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"72c688f1-386a-43a0-95f4-601576d7939e","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:05:07.312Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
