{"parentUuid":"27b5d960-f718-49d9-bc1f-cdff77db4c13","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcvxgjKMmZzG3jLPVCaEz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012iUUtVd4Vfs3u3yfmCJNP8","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/implementation-progress.md","old_string":"## NEXT\n- Run the full existing suite (unit + integration) for no-regression (AC11),\n  then coverage gate check, then the pre-report self-check (diff-vs-plan,\n  security quick scan) and `.pipeline/surface-delta.md`.","new_string":"## Unit 3 — full-suite no-regression + coverage gate + self-check (DONE)\n\n- Ran `pytest -q -m \"not perf\" --cov=src --cov-branch --cov-report=term-missing`\n  twice (once before the turn-cap resume, once after, both in this session)\n  against the live Postgres/Redis testcontainers: **253 passed, 3 skipped, 1\n  deselected (the `perf` marker, per CLAUDE.md's CI convention), 0 failed**\n  both times. Coverage: **89% overall** (branch), clearing the ≥85% gate. New\n  modules (`schemas/usage_daily.py`, `services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n  `routes/usage_daily.py`) are all at 100%; `repositories/usage_repo.py` is at\n  89% (the few uncovered lines are pre-existing gaps in `count_usage_rollups`\n  unrelated to this change, plus one coverage.py multi-line-comprehension\n  quirk on the new function's `return [...]` line, which both the happy-path\n  and empty-day integration tests do exercise).\n- AC11 (no-regression): confirmed both by the unchanged existing suites\n  passing and by `test_existing_usage_endpoint_unchanged` (new, in\n  `test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`) directly asserting `POST /v1/events` +\n  `GET /v1/usage` still behave as before with the new router mounted.\n- Pre-report self-check (code-standards step 6):\n  - **Diff vs plan**: `git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others\n    --exclude-standard` show exactly the plan's 7 files (schemas/service/route\n    new, `usage_repo.py`/`main.py` additive-mod, 2 new test files) plus\n    pre-existing unrelated modifications to `.claude/settings.json`/`PROJECT.md`\n    (PROJECT.md's diff is the feature-brief swap itself, already present before\n    this session started).\n  - **Hardcoded secrets**: grep across all 7 changed/new files — no hits.\n  - **Missing RLS**: `aggregate_daily_event_counts` scopes `WHERE api_key_id =\n    :api_key_id` first (bound from `principal.api_key_id`, never client\n    input), inside `scoped_transaction` (RLS backstop) — confirmed by reading\n    the function and the cross-tenant integration test passing.\n  - **Unsanitized inputs**: the only input (`date`) flows\n    `DailyUsageQueryParams` (`extra=\"forbid\"`) -> `parse_daily_date` (anchored\n    regex + calendar + range check) before any use; no raw\n    `request.query_params` access in the route/service.\n- App boot verified twice this session: `import src.main` succeeds, and a\n  real `uvicorn src.main:app` process answers `GET /health` with 200\n  `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`.\n- `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` rewritten for this feature (the file on disk\n  was stale content from the prior quota-admin feature run — overwritten,\n  not appended).\n\n## STATUS: DONE\n\nAll 3 units complete, full suite green (253 passed / 0 failed / 89% branch\ncoverage), app boots, surface-delta + progress notes current. Ready for the\nsecurity/testing/documentation stages."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":430,"cache_read_input_tokens":160793,"output_tokens":1388,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":430},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":13