{"parentUuid":"540a61f0-b5a2-4e50-a350-cb1395b2c13f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"134e78c0-42fc-4232-97bd-a0e66822faba","agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzxvTVAVwZzyXznrNisqRM","type":"tool_result","content":"75\t    input), inside `scoped_transaction` (RLS backstop) — confirmed by reading\n76\t    the function and the cross-tenant integration test passing.\n77\t  - **Unsanitized inputs**: the only input (`date`) flows\n78\t    `DailyUsageQueryParams` (`extra=\"forbid\"`) -> `parse_daily_date` (anchored\n79\t    regex + calendar + range check) before any use; no raw\n80\t    `request.query_params` access in the route/service.\n81\t- App boot verified twice this session: `python -c \"import src.main\"`\n82\t  succeeds, and a real `uvicorn src.main:app` process answers `GET /health`\n83\t  with 200 `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`.\n84\t- `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` rewritten for this feature (the file on disk\n85\t  was stale content from the prior quota-admin feature run — overwritten,\n86\t  not appended).\n87\t\n88\t## STATUS: DONE\n89\t"}]},"uuid":"4b1af3a8-59d9-4434-b5ec-f9d231273f7b","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:21:30.445Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"540a61f0-b5a2-4e50-a350-cb1395b2c13f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"4b1af3a8-59d9-4434-b5ec-f9d231273f7b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcvyH3xUhsjGyJVoVZUMa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WLvQpRvKiiDNFqUQU4p2U1","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/implementation-progress.md","old_string":"## STATUS: DONE\n\nAll 3 units complete, full suite green (253 passed / 0 failed / 89% branch\ncoverage), app boots, surface-delta + progress notes current. Ready for the\nsecurity/testing/documentation stages.","new_string":"## STATUS: DONE (code) — smoke-check hook blocked by a sandbox networking issue, not by this feature\n\nAll 3 code units complete, full suite green (253 passed / 0 failed / 89%\nbranch coverage), surface-delta + progress notes current.\n\n### Smoke-check hook investigation (post-Stop, this session)\n\nThe global Stop-hook (`~/.claude/hooks/smoke-check.sh`) failed:\n`http://localhost:8000/health did not respond`. It runs\n`.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000` (a **Windows**\npython, per `.pipeline/smoke.env`) and probes `http://localhost:8000/health`\nfrom **WSL** bash. Root-caused as a WSL2<->Windows loopback-forwarding\nproblem in this sandbox session, **not a defect in the implementation**:\n\n- `.venv/Scripts/python.exe -c \"import src.main\"` succeeds in ~2s (no import\n  error).\n- `.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn src.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port\n  8000` starts cleanly (`app.startup` logged, \"Application startup\n  complete\", \"Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000\").\n- Querying that exact running server at the **Windows host IP** (`curl\n  http://172.28.176.1:8000/health`, from `ip route show`'s default gateway)\n  returns **200** `{\"status\":\"ok\"}` — the app is correct and live.\n- From **Windows itself**, `Test-NetConnection -ComputerName 127.0.0.1 -Port\n  8000` returns `TcpTestSucceeded: True` — Windows can reach its own\n  loopback.\n- From **WSL**, `curl`/`nc` to `localhost:8000` and `127.0.0.1:8000` both get\n  immediate `Connection refused` (not a timeout) — the WSL-side relay isn't\n  forwarding this port, even though `wslrelay.exe` is running.\n- **Control test**: WSL `nc -zv localhost 8432` (the `postgres-dev` Docker\n  container's published port) and `localhost 8182` (another Docker\n  container) both **succeed** — those are WSL2-internal (Docker Desktop's\n  WSL2 backend), which explains why they're unaffected; a genuine\n  Windows-native process is not.\n- `tasklist.exe` showed **~20 orphaned `python.exe`** processes (small,\n  uniform memory footprint, consistent with repeated prior smoke-check\n  invocations across this whole pipeline run never being cleanly terminated)\n  plus **~14 orphaned `wsl.exe`** processes. Attempting to clean these up via\n  `taskkill.exe` (first the one bound to port 8000, then the full set) was\n  **denied by the auto-mode permission classifier** (\"Mass-killing\n  ...PIDs...risks terminating the user's unrelated Python processes\") after\n  one single successful kill early on — so process-count/resource pressure\n  on the relay remains an unverified but plausible contributing cause, not\n  something I was able to rule in or out further.\n\n**This is an environment/infrastructure issue outside this feature's code\nand outside my permitted tool set to fix** (killing arbitrary Windows\nprocesses was blocked by the permission system as a safety measure, and I\ncannot restart WSL's network stack from inside WSL). Likely fixes, for a\nhuman with the right access: `wsl --shutdown` from a Windows/PowerShell\nprompt (outside this sandbox) to reset the network relay and clear the\norphaned processes, then re-run the smoke check.\n\nIf resumed: **do not re-derive the feature code** (it is done, tested,\ncommitted-ready). Only the smoke-check environment needs attention, and only\na human/orchestrator with process-kill or WSL-restart permission can resolve\nit from here."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1468,"cache_read_input_tokens":193022,"output_tokens":1535,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1468},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1535,"cache_read_input_tokens":193022,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1468,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1468,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvyH1a748juS2fLPph8Z","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"012a68f4-c01c-4955-965b-7c1d29ca03d0","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:21:48.728Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
