{"parentUuid":"bf6f485e-fd09-453f-80eb-68f40902d3fd","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcvyJPx2zvW1wE75Nsp6r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nThe feature implementation is complete, tested, and verified correct — but the Stop-hook's smoke check failed for an environment reason unrelated to the code, and I've hit a permission boundary trying to fix it. Reporting both clearly:\n\n**Feature status: done.** `GET /v1/usage/daily` is fully implemented per the plan (files listed in my previous message), the full test suite passes (253 passed, 0 failed, 3 skipped/1 deselected for the `perf` marker, 89% branch coverage, ≥85% gate met), and the app boots correctly.\n\n**Smoke-check hook failure — root cause is a WSL2↔Windows networking issue, not my code:**\n- The hook runs `.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn ...` (Windows Python) and probes `http://localhost:8000/health` from WSL bash.\n- I confirmed the app imports cleanly, starts cleanly, and — when queried at the Windows host's actual IP (`http://172.28.176.1:8000/health`) — returns `200 {\"status\":\"ok\"}`. From Windows itself, `Test-NetConnection 127.0.0.1:8000` succeeds.\n- From WSL, `curl`/`nc` to `localhost:8000`/`127.0.0.1:8000` get immediate `Connection refused`, while WSL-internal Docker-published ports (8432, 8182) connect fine — isolating the failure to WSL's loopback-forwarding of genuine Windows-native processes, not to the app.\n- `tasklist.exe` showed ~20 orphaned `python.exe` and ~14 orphaned `wsl.exe` processes, almost certainly left over from repeated smoke-check attempts across this pipeline run. I killed one (freeing port 8000) but further cleanup attempts (single-PID and mass) were **denied by the auto-mode permission classifier** as a safety measure against killing processes I couldn't verifiably prove I created.\n\nI did not find a way to resolve this within my permitted tools. A human with Windows access can very likely fix it with `wsl --shutdown` (outside this sandbox) to reset the network relay and clear the orphaned processes, then re-run the smoke check — the underlying app has already been shown to work correctly.\n\nFiles: `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/implementation-progress.md` has the full investigation trail (so a resumed session doesn't re-derive the finished feature code). All feature files are unchanged from my last report: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`, `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` (additive), `src/main.py` (additive), `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`, `.pipeline/surface-delta.md`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1644,"cache_read_input_tokens":194490,"output_tokens":996,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1644},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":996,"cache_read_input_tokens":194490,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1644,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvyJNLoPQcMHv87zERX5","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"1b8ae52c-c622-4d3e-bceb-4066f346c236","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:21:59.801Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
