{"parentUuid":"5ae580aa-0608-4715-932e-29ec2da45b97","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"134e78c0-42fc-4232-97bd-a0e66822faba","agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SUsuyS3ygzU8H9ZdDz3P79","type":"tool_result","content":"88\t## STATUS: DONE (code) — smoke-check hook blocked by a sandbox networking issue, not by this feature\n89\t\n90\tAll 3 code units complete, full suite green (253 passed / 0 failed / 89%\n91\tbranch coverage), surface-delta + progress notes current.\n92\t\n93\t### Smoke-check hook investigation (post-Stop, this session)\n94\t\n95\tThe global Stop-hook (`~/.claude/hooks/smoke-check.sh`) failed:\n96\t`http://localhost:8000/health did not respond`. It runs\n97\t`.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000` (a **Windows**"}]},"uuid":"a9c17e7b-faf4-4fbd-b567-e98928ab9998","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:24:20.375Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5ae580aa-0608-4715-932e-29ec2da45b97","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"a9c17e7b-faf4-4fbd-b567-e98928ab9998","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcvyVajEsdzHH9xGgKF3E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0116qfxbzuoNdshxr2wkg1c6","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/implementation-progress.md","old_string":"If resumed: **do not re-derive the feature code** (it is done, tested,\ncommitted-ready). Only the smoke-check environment needs attention, and only\na human/orchestrator with process-kill or WSL-restart permission can resolve\nit from here.","new_string":"If resumed: **do not re-derive the feature code** (it is done, tested,\ncommitted-ready). Only the smoke-check environment needs attention, and only\na human/orchestrator with process-kill or WSL-restart permission can resolve\nit from here.\n\n### Second pass, after a second identical Stop-hook failure\n\nRe-investigated with a sharper hypothesis: my own earlier orphaned process\n(PID 10544, self-created this session, log-provenance confirmed via\n`Started server process [10544]` in my own captured log file) was still\nsquatting on port 8000, and Windows' `SO_REUSEADDR` semantics could let a\nsecond listener silently coexist on the same port without a bind error while\nbreaking connection routing. This was a legitimate, single, session-tracked\nkill (not a mass/pattern kill), so `taskkill.exe /F /PID 10544` was\npermitted and succeeded.\n\n**Result: the port-squatting theory was ruled out, not confirmed.** With\nport 8000 fully clear and exactly **one** clean process running (confirmed\nvia `netstat.exe -ano` before and after each attempt):\n- `.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000` (smoke's\n  exact command, binds `127.0.0.1` only) → WSL `curl localhost:8000/health`\n  still `Connection refused` immediately.\n- The same server rebound with `--host 0.0.0.0` → WSL `curl\n  localhost:8000/health` **still** `Connection refused`, while `curl\n  http://172.28.176.1:8000/health` (the Windows host IP) **still returns\n  200** cleanly.\n\nSo with a provably clean, single, correctly-bound listener, WSL's\n`localhost`/`127.0.0.1` forwarding to a genuine Windows-native process is\nstill broken, while the app itself is still demonstrably correct at the host\nIP. This confirms the earlier diagnosis was right for the wrong extra\nreason: it is a **WSL2<->Windows loopback-forwarding defect in this sandbox\nsession**, independent of process cleanliness. I cleaned up both\nself-created test processes (10544, then the two from this second pass)\nafter each check, so no orphans of mine remain contributing further noise.\n\n**I do not have a way to fix this from inside WSL** (no permission to touch\nWindows' network stack/firewall/relay, and `wsl --shutdown` must run from\noutside this sandbox on the Windows host). The feature code has been\nindependently verified correct through: the full pytest suite (real\nPostgres/Redis via testcontainers, 253/253 passing), a direct Linux-venv\n`uvicorn` + `curl localhost` health check earlier this session (200, within\none network namespace), and now three separate confirmations that the\nWindows-venv server answers correctly at the host IP. Further retries of the\nStop-hook will hit the same environmental wall until a human resets WSL's\nnetworking from the Windows side."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":448,"cache_read_input_tokens":204913,"output_tokens":1233,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":448},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1233,"cache_read_input_tokens":204913,"cache_creation_input_tokens":448,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":448,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvyVY7yJS8qG8f677aJ5","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"9161c4e1-444c-41a8-b33c-f20dde8e8632","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:24:34.978Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
