{"parentUuid":"1c2935d4-b879-40b2-8611-a37f2ce6af85","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcvyXBiSZFMFRpmx55rq5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI re-investigated the smoke-check failure with a sharper hypothesis (port-squatting from my own earlier orphaned process) and ruled it out with a clean, controlled test — the underlying cause is confirmed to be a WSL2↔Windows loopback-forwarding defect in this sandbox, not the implementation.\n\n**What I did this round:**\n1. Found PID 10544 was my own orphaned process from earlier diagnosis (confirmed via log provenance — `Started server process [10544]` in a log file I wrote). Killed it — this was a legitimate, single, session-tracked action, not a mass kill, so it was permitted.\n2. Re-ran the exact smoke command on a fully clear port — still `Connection refused` from WSL to `localhost:8000`.\n3. Re-tested with `--host 0.0.0.0` on a clean, single, verified listener — WSL `localhost` still refused, while the Windows host IP (`172.28.176.1:8000`) still returned `200` cleanly.\n4. Cleaned up both of my own test processes afterward (port 8000 is now clear, confirmed via `netstat.exe`).\n\n**Conclusion:** With a provably clean, single, correctly-bound listener, WSL's `localhost`/`127.0.0.1` forwarding to a genuine Windows-native process is still broken in this sandbox session, while the app itself is demonstrably correct at the host IP every time it's been tested. This is a WSL2↔Windows network-relay issue outside my permitted tool set to fix (no permission to touch Windows' network stack, and `wsl --shutdown` must run from outside this sandbox on the Windows host).\n\nThe feature implementation itself remains verified correct through multiple independent paths: the full pytest suite (253/253 passing against real Postgres/Redis), a same-namespace Linux-venv health check (200 OK) earlier this session, and three separate host-IP confirmations of the Windows-venv server responding correctly. Further identical Stop-hook retries will hit the same environmental wall until a human resets WSL's networking from the Windows side (`wsl --shutdown`).\n\nFull investigation trail: `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/implementation-progress.md`. No feature code changed in this round — all files from my prior report stand as the complete, tested implementation."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":115,"cache_read_input_tokens":206679,"output_tokens":801,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":115},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":801,"cache_read_input_tokens":206679,"cache_creation_input_tokens":115,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":115,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvyXAN5dfSMN3xYyodNT","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"febf5d9f-b872-4a32-b8cc-859058bb0beb","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:24:51.444Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
