{"parentUuid":"c61e93b2-8eff-4157-a7d9-e013383f12ee","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9897bafc5c9b12b7","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcvyamCRMz1REp32ruCjc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01U2JoSsotcgPNF6PKznwzZm","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/smoke.env","old_string":"export SMOKE_START_CMD=\".venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000\"\nexport SMOKE_HEALTH_URL=\"http://localhost:8000/health\"\nexport SMOKE_BUILD_CMD='.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m scripts.smoke_import_check'","new_string":"export SMOKE_START_CMD=\".venv/Scripts/python.exe -m uvicorn src.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000\"\nif grep -qi microsoft /proc/version 2>/dev/null; then\n  # WSL2 sandbox override (see .pipeline/implementation-progress.md for the\n  # full diagnosis): 'localhost'/127.0.0.1 does not reliably forward from WSL\n  # to a genuine Windows-native process (.venv/Scripts/python.exe) in this\n  # environment — repeated, isolated tests (clean single listener, --host\n  # 0.0.0.0, both localhost and the gateway IP probed back-to-back) show\n  # WSL curl to localhost getting \"Connection refused\" while the exact same\n  # running server answers 200 at the default-route gateway IP every time.\n  # Windows itself (Test-NetConnection) and Docker-published ports (which are\n  # WSL2-internal) are both unaffected, isolating this to WSL's loopback\n  # relay for native Windows listeners specifically. Route the health probe\n  # to the gateway IP instead, where the 0.0.0.0-bound server is actually\n  # reachable from inside WSL; a non-WSL run (plain Linux) keeps localhost.\n  export SMOKE_HEALTH_URL=\"http://$(ip route show default | awk '{print $3}'):8000/health\"\nelse\n  export SMOKE_HEALTH_URL=\"http://localhost:8000/health\"\nfi\nexport SMOKE_BUILD_CMD='.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m scripts.smoke_import_check'"